cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method for efficient inference in convolutional neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The proposed method involves a probabilistic model and training mechanisms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions pruning subsets of CNNs, which is a common technique in neural network compression, indicating that it could also fit in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of mixture models and the probabilistic approach could also suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experiments on image classification and semantic segmentation, which are tasks related to multimedia and multimodal processing, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
